article.description: Adrian Ritchie scored 15 points to lead four players in double figures and Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) beat Marquette 66-50 on Friday night.
article.headline: Wisconsin-Green Bay beats Marquette behind balanced attack
article.story:
GREEN BAY, Wis. -- Adrian Ritchie scored 15 points to lead four players in double figures and help Wisconsin-Green Bay (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 23 AP) beat Marquette 66-50 on Friday night.

Julie Wojta had 12 points and 12 rebounds, and Lydia Bauer scored 12 points and grabbed 10 boards for the Phoenix (6-0), who avenged a three-point loss to Marquette last year -- Green Bay's only loss in the regular season.

Green Bay led 29-28 at halftime thanks to 15 turnovers and 13 fouls that gave the Golden Eagles plenty of opportunities to score.

Katherine Plouffe scored 15 points to lead Marquette (4-4), which made just two field goals over the final 9 minutes of the game.
